Method Detail

generateUVCoordinates

public static VertexBuffer generateUVCoordinates(int texco,
                                                 int projection,
                                                 int textureDimension,
                                                 int[] coordinatesSwappingIndexes,
                                                 java.util.List<Geometry> geometries)
This method generates UV coordinates for the given mesh. IMPORTANT! This method assumes that all geometries represent one node. Each containing mesh with separate material. So all meshes have the same reference to vertex table which stores all their vertices.

Parameters:
texco - texture coordinates type
projection - the projection type for 2D textures
textureDimension - the dimension of the texture (only 2D and 3D)
coordinatesSwappingIndexes - an array that tells how UV-coordinates need to be swapped
geometries - a list of geometries the UV coordinates will be applied to
Returns:
created UV-coordinates buffer
